{
  "stem": "10905.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, of course, then with the practicing Jews, who were practicing Jews, in that they had Jewish homes and observed all the holidays, but they did not necessarily keep a kosher home.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, those who were from the Satmar, they dress like they still do in Williamsburg today-- Williamsburg, New York, not Williamsburg, Virginia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the others were very, very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, the only way you could really tell is, on a very hot day, perhaps, when nobody else would be wearing a hat, they'd be wearing a hat-- the men, that is.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The women really did not wear Sheitels, except for the very orthodox and very religious.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Although, in my family, some wore Sheitels, and others did not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But primarily, the people that-- in our circle-- not necessarily our family, but our circle were mainly practicing Jews who knew they would were Jewish, who were Zionists and non-kosher.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I have to tell you that my time in Subotica was limited.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- that's not-- that's where I was born.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was a physician.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a pediatrician.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he had practiced in Subotica, and we also lived in Belgrade, Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And until the war, primarily Belgrade is where we lived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When we came back, the war had already started, and obviously some things a little bit different then, because then the war was on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I would say that Jews and non-Jews lived together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no such thing as a ghetto, if that's the question.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, just the same way that there are Jewish neighborhoods and Chinese neighborhoods and black neighborhoods and Hispanic neighborhoods, some by social need, some by desire, but there was no specific ghetto, if that's what you're alluding to.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
